         <t:abstract>
            <t:p>The <t:foreign xml:lang="gez">Maṣḥafa ṭomār</t:foreign> narrates how a letter urging the people to respect the Sunday rest appeared outside a Church of Rome in which the patriarch Athanasius celebrated mass.
         </t:p>
            <t:p>There exists a short version (most frequent) and a long version, the latter begins with መጽሐፈ፡ ጦማር፡ ዘወረደትት፡ እምሰማይ፡ ላዕለ፡ እደ፡
               አትናቴዎስ</t:p>
         </t:abstract>
